44
00:06:13,840 --> 00:06:24,310
Karin watched them. Her eyes went from her
sister, to Howard, and back again to her sister.

45
00:06:24,310 --> 00:06:25,310
She smiled.

46
00:06:25,310 --> 00:06:32,069
It was not a nice smile.

47
00:06:32,069 --> 00:06:41,870
Every Sunday morning after that, Marcia brought
Howard home for a glass of wine after church.

48
00:06:41,870 --> 00:06:50,080
Howard stopped his car in the street outside
the apartment building, and Marcia said, 'Sound

49
00:06:50,080 --> 00:06:58,410
the horn, Howard. Tell Karin we're here, then
she can get the wine ready.'

50
00:06:58,410 --> 00:07:08,729
So Howard gave three little toots on his car
horn. On sunny days, Karin always came to

51
00:07:08,729 --> 00:07:15,789
the wall at the edge of the roof, and looked
over to wave at them. Then she went to get

52
00:07:15,789 --> 00:07:17,360
the wine.

53
00:07:17,360 --> 00:07:28,910
She always wore her bikini or a very short
skirt. Marcia never wore short skirts or a

54
00:07:28,910 --> 00:07:30,400
bikini.

55
00:07:30,400 --> 00:07:42,360
'My legs are too fat for bikinis,' she told
Howard. 'Your legs are... very nice,' he said

56
00:07:42,360 --> 00:07:45,780
shyly.

57
00:07:45,780 --> 00:07:56,639
One day in June Karin asked Howard, 'What
time do you finish work, Howard?'

58
00:07:56,639 --> 00:08:00,009
'About six o'clock,' he said.

59
00:08:00,009 --> 00:08:09,930
'Could you bring me home after work?' Karin
said. 'My shop's very near the hospital - you

60
00:08:09,930 --> 00:08:16,289
drive right past it. And you only live three
streets away from us.'

61
00:08:16,289 --> 00:08:28,270
'There's a very good bus,' said Marcia quickly.
'It stops outside our building.'

62
00:08:28,270 --> 00:08:37,140
'But the bus is so slow!' Karin said. 'Please,
Howard!'

63
00:08:37,140 --> 00:08:46,321
Howard looked from one sister to the other.
'Oh, well... er, yes, all right then,' he

64
00:08:46,321 --> 00:08:47,530
said.

65
00:08:47,530 --> 00:08:55,990
'Thank you!' Karin said, and gave him a quick
kiss.

66
00:08:55,990 --> 00:09:06,450
So every evening Howard drove Karin home.
On the first Friday, they were an hour late.

67
00:09:06,450 --> 00:09:14,090
When they arrived, Marcia was at the door
of the apartment building.

68
00:09:14,090 --> 00:09:22,070
'What happened?' she asked. 'Why are you so
late?'

69
00:09:22,070 --> 00:09:33,010
'There was an accident,' Karin said. 'Three
cars, all across the road - on that hill by

70
00:09:33,010 --> 00:09:44,120
the cinema, you know. We couldn't get past,
we couldn't go back. There were so many cars!

71
00:09:44,120 --> 00:09:48,670
