82
00:11:03,920 --> 00:11:17,330
'Stop it, Karin!' Marcia said. 'Don't say
those things!' Karin laughed. 'What's the

83
00:11:17,330 --> 00:11:24,149
matter, big sister? Are you afraid I'm going
to take him from you?'

84
00:11:24,149 --> 00:11:29,230
Marcia did not answer.

85
00:11:29,230 --> 00:11:35,540
The next Sunday, Howard phoned Marcia early
in the morning.

86
00:11:35,540 --> 00:11:44,820
'I - I don't feel very well,' he said. 'I'm
not going to church today.'

87
00:11:44,820 --> 00:11:54,089
'My love, I'm sorry,' Marcia said. 'Can I
phone you when I get home?'

88
00:11:54,089 --> 00:11:58,160
'Yes, of course,' he said.

89
00:11:58,160 --> 00:12:07,550
'I can't phone before one o'clock,' Marcia
said. 'I'm going to be late back because there's

90
00:12:07,550 --> 00:12:13,240
a meeting after church. Something about Africa,
I think.'

91
00:12:13,240 --> 00:12:18,550
'Oh yes, I remember,' Howard said.

92
00:12:18,550 --> 00:12:29,180
But Marcia was wrong. There was no meeting
after church that morning. It was the next

93
00:12:29,180 --> 00:12:37,820
Sunday. So she left church at the usual time
and arrived home at a quarter to twelve.

94
00:12:37,820 --> 00:12:49,810
First, she went in to see her father, but
he was asleep. Then she phoned Howard, but

95
00:12:49,810 --> 00:12:51,740
there was no answer.

96
00:12:51,740 --> 00:13:01,770
'Perhaps he's sleeping,' she thought. 'And
his mother doesn't want to answer the phone.'

97
00:13:01,770 --> 00:13:12,579
She went to her room and put on a long summer
skirt. Then she went up to the roof garden.

98
00:13:12,579 --> 00:13:24,180
