101
00:13:40,910 --> 00:13:52,500
'I feel bad about this,' Howard said. 'We
must tell Marcia soon, Karin.'

102
00:13:52,500 --> 00:14:03,420
'No!' Karin said quickly. She gave a little
laugh. 'It's our secret, Howard. Only for

103
00:14:03,420 --> 00:14:08,470
a little longer. All right?'

104
00:14:08,470 --> 00:14:12,959
'I - I don't like...' he began.

105
00:14:12,959 --> 00:14:26,740
'But you do love me, Howard,' Karin said.
'Not Marcia? Say you love me. Please!'

106
00:14:26,740 --> 00:14:29,550
Marcia suddenly felt cold.

107
00:14:29,550 --> 00:14:39,350
'You... you know I do,' Howard answered. 'But-'

108
00:14:39,350 --> 00:14:50,269
Karin kissed him. 'It's our little secret.
Oh, is your car outside, my love? We don't

109
00:14:50,269 --> 00:14:52,680
want Marcia to see it.'

110
00:14:52,680 --> 00:15:01,410
'I didn't bring my car,' Howard said. 'I walked
here.'

111
00:15:01,410 --> 00:15:12,070
'Good,' Karin said. 'But it's getting late.
You must go, before she comes home.'

112
00:15:12,070 --> 00:15:14,600
They kissed again.

113
00:15:14,600 --> 00:15:23,880
'See you tomorrow, usual time, usual place,'
said Karin. 'Now, go!'

114
00:15:23,880 --> 00:15:32,650
Marcia moved quickly and quietly away from
the roof door, and ran to her bedroom. She

115
00:15:32,650 --> 00:15:38,149
did not want Howard or Karin to see her.

116
00:15:38,149 --> 00:15:47,230
She heard their voices. Then the front door
of the apartment opened and closed. Howard

117
00:15:47,230 --> 00:15:49,410
was gone.

118
00:15:49,410 --> 00:16:04,970
Marcia sat on her bed for an hour. 'Why, why,
why?' she thought. 'Why does she do it? I

119
00:16:04,970 --> 00:16:15,079
stay at home with an old man all the time.
I can't go out to work, I can't make new friends,

120
00:16:15,079 --> 00:16:26,570
I can't meet new people. I go shopping once
a week and I go to church once a week. That's

121
00:16:26,570 --> 00:16:41,380
all. And then I met Howard. When he said "I
love you", I was so happy. And now...?'

122
00:16:41,380 --> 00:16:53,139
Karin had everything. Good looks, a job, friends.
She was young, she was beautiful, she could

123
00:16:53,139 --> 00:17:02,089
have any man. So why Howard? Why, why, why?

124
00:17:02,089 --> 00:17:11,559
'It's not because she wants him,' Marcia thought.
'It's because I love him. It's because she

125
00:17:11,559 --> 00:17:13,919
doesn't want me to be happy.'

126
00:17:13,919 --> 00:17:22,650
But you do love me, Howard. Not Marcia?

127
00:17:22,650 --> 00:17:26,010
You know I do.

128
00:17:26,010 --> 00:17:37,380
Was it true? Did Howard love Karin and not
her? No! He saw only the beautiful, suntanned

129
00:17:37,380 --> 00:17:41,580
body. He didn't know her.

130
00:17:41,580 --> 00:17:47,180
'She's not going to have him...' Marcia thought.

131
00:17:47,180 --> 00:17:57,190
Every evening that week, Howard drove Karin
home after work. And every evening they got

132
00:17:57,190 --> 00:18:01,230
later and later.

133
00:18:01,230 --> 00:18:07,530
